[Nail-patella syndrome].

[Article in German]

Wildfeuer T(1), Albrecht G.

Author information:
(1)Dermatologische Abteilung, Krankenhauses Spandau, Berlin.

The nail-patella syndrome is an autosomal dominant trait characterized by 
abnormalities of the nails, patella and radial head, iliac crest and, in some 
cases, nephropathy. The genetic defect is localized on chromosome 9q34.1. The 
clinical features in affected individuals vary greatly. The nephropathy may 
progress to end-stage renal failure, leading to decreased life expectancy. We 
report a woman with bilateral hypoplastic thumbnails, who also had aplasia of 
both patellae and subluxation of the left elbow joint with hypoplasia of the 
radial head. The mother and the sister of the patient had similar changes and 
also suffered from nephropathy.

